description.value: These are example instances that show what data produced and consumed by systems conforming with this implementation guide might look like.
These are resources that are used within this implementation guide that do not fit into one of the other categories.
Receive: Patient is admitted, message is corrected due to incorrect hospital department
Receive: Patient is admitted, message is corrected due to incorrect time of admission
Receive: Patient is admitted as emergency, patient is admitted as inpatient, patient is discharged
Receive: Patient is admitted, patient is registered as being on leave, patient returns from leave, patient is discharged
Receive: Patient is admitted, patient is registered as being on leave, patient doesn't return from leave, patient is discharged
Receive: Patient is admitted, patient is registered as being on leave, patient returns from leave, patient is registered as dead
Receive: Patient is admitted, 'patient is registered as being on leave, patient returns from leave', ' to ' x 2
Receive: Patient is admitted, message is corrected due to incorrect hospital department
Receive: Patient is admitted, message is corrected due to incorrect time of admission
Receive dublicate: Patient is admitted, doesn't get acknowledged, patient is admitted
Receive: Receive cancellation of admit patient: Patient is admitted, correction of admit patient and cancellation admit patient
Receive: Messages received in wrong order: Patient is admitted as emergency, patient is discharged, patient is admitted as inpatient.
Receive: Receive a message with different timezones (+01:00 and +02:00): Patient is admitted in one timezone, patient is discharged in a different timezone.
Receive: Receive a message on the 29th of February 2024 (leap year): Patient is admitted on the date of leap year
Receive: Receive a message where the serviceprovider is different from the sender: Patient is admitted
Send: Register patient as acute ambulant, correct message due to incorrect hospital department
Send: Register patient as acute ambulant, correct message due to incorrect time of admission.
Send: Register patient as acute ambulant, admit patient (inpatient), discharge patient
Send: Admit patient, register patient as being on leave, register patient as returned from leave, discharge patient.
Send: Admit patient, register patient as being on leave, patient doesn't return from leave, discharge patient.
Send: Admit patient, register patient as being on leave, patient returns from leave, patient dies
Send: Admit patient, *register patient as being on leave, patient returns from leave*, * to * x2
Send: Admit patient, correct message due to incorrect hospital department. Evaluation is based on SOR number.
Send: Admit patient, correct message due to incorrect time of admission.
Send: Cancel a corrected admission: Admit patient, correct admit patient and cancel admit patient
Send: Send a message on the 29th of February 2024 (leap year)
Send: Send dublicate: Admit patient, doesn't get acknowledged, send admit patient. IDs are handled correct
Send: Admit patient and End hospital stay in different timezones. Correct use of timezone of summertime (+02:00) and vintertime (+01:00).
